<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-395-524  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 395 524.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Programming Languages andamp; Systems  Jan 1990 v12n1 p123(12).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A correctness proof for combinator reduction with cycles.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Farmer, William M.; Ramsdell, John D.; Watro, Ronald J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The theoretical foundation of a technique of Wadsworth,popularized by Turner, in which a cyclic graph rewriting rule isused to implement reduction of the fixed point combinator Y isexamined.andP;  The work is inapplicable to the cyclic Y rule, which isunsound in this sense since graph normal forms can exist withoutcorresponding term normal forms.andP;  Combinator head reduction usingthe cyclic Y rule is defined and proven correct; the correctnessof normal reduction is an immediate consequence.andP;  A method forconsidering reduction with cycles as an optimization of reductionwithout cycles is presented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Programming InstructionProgramming LanguagesTheorySemanticsGraph Theory.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>